What:		/sys/bus/platform/devices/INOU0000:XX/cpu_pl4
Date:		April 2026
KernelVersion:	7.3
Contact:	Erhan Bilgili <nano.matters.code@gmail.com>
Description:
		Allows userspace applications to set the CPU PL4 (peak power limit) in watts. The
		acceptable range is device specific and can be queried via cpu_pl4_min and
		cpu_pl4_max. On devices with "double PL4" support, the EC stores half the actual
		value internally but the sysfs interface always operates in effective watts.

		Reading this file returns the current PL4 value in watts.

